{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567000","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567000"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18916"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18916","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18916"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.87,0.05,0.01,0.05,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11649"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112485"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11649","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11649"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18916"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94516"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4956"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11349"},{"type":"tags","id":"11358"},{"type":"tags","id":"11361"},{"type":"tags","id":"11363"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27400"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27401"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45085"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46159"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112485","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/112485"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old woman with moderate intellectual disability presents to the clinic with her support worker for a routine health check. She appears anxious and has difficulty understanding complex medical terminology.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate approach to providing care for this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Direct all questions and explanations to the patient using simple language","Speak more slowly and loudly to ensure comprehension","Request immediate psychiatric assessment","Refer all communication through the support worker","Defer history and examination until a family member is present"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edirect all questions and explanations to the patient using simple language\u003C/strong\u003E. This respects the patient\u0027s autonomy and dignity while ensuring effective communication. Healthcare providers should adjust their communication style to meet the patient\u0027s needs, using clear, simple language and checking understanding frequently.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are not optimal first-line strategies because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpeak more slowly and loudly to ensure comprehension\u003C/strong\u003E - This confuses intellectual disability with hearing impairment and may be patronising. Speaking loudly does not address comprehension difficulties related to intellectual disability\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequest immediate psychiatric assessment\u003C/strong\u003E - This inappropriately assumes psychiatric needs and stigmatises intellectual disability\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERefer all communication through the support worker\u003C/strong\u003E - This excludes the patient from their own care decisions and fails to respect their autonomy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDefer history and examination until a family member is present\u003C/strong\u003E - This unnecessarily delays care and assumes family members are required for communication\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile support workers and family members can provide valuable assistance, the primary approach should always be direct communication with the patient using appropriate language. This promotes dignity, autonomy, and patient-centred care.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Healthcare providers must obtain informed consent from substitute decision makers when patients lack capacity to make their own medical decisions.","Patients with intellectual disabilities should be included in discussions about their care using appropriate communication methods.","Healthcare providers have a duty to advocate for reasonable adjustments to ensure equitable access to healthcare for patients with disabilities."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 18]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94516"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18916"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94516","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94516"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-01T18:35:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-01T18:36:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11649"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112485"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading